@echo off
echo ============================================================================\necho 🔧 TROUBLESHOOTING: Check Stock Button Missing\necho ============================================================================\necho.\necho The \"Check Stock\" button should appear next to \"Add Product\" button.\necho If it's missing, follow these steps:\necho.\necho 1. CLEAR BROWSER CACHE\necho    - Press Ctrl+F5 (Windows) or Cmd+Shift+R (Mac)\necho    - Or manually clear cache in browser settings\necho.\necho 2. CHECK IF YOU'RE ON THE RIGHT PAGE\necho    - URL should be: http://localhost:3000/seller/products\necho    - Make sure you're logged in as a SELLER (not BUYER)\necho.\necho 3. RESTART SERVERS\necho    - Stop your React frontend (Ctrl+C)\necho    - Stop your Spring Boot backend (Ctrl+C)\necho    - Restart backend: cd backend && mvn spring-boot:run\necho    - Restart frontend: cd frontend && npm start\necho.\necho 4. CHECK BROWSER CONSOLE\necho    - Press F12 to open DevTools\necho    - Look for JavaScript errors in Console tab\necho    - Look for failed API calls in Network tab\necho.\necho 5. VERIFY FILE CHANGES\necho    - Check that SellerProducts.js was saved correctly\necho    - Look for \"Check Stock\" button code in the file\necho.\necho 6. TEST WITH SAMPLE HTML\necho    - Open test-check-stock-button.html in your browser\necho    - This shows how the buttons should look\necho.\necho ============================================================================\necho 📊 EXPECTED STOCK MANAGEMENT FEATURES:\necho ============================================================================\necho.\necho ✅ Blue \"Check Stock\" button next to pink \"Add Product\" button\necho ✅ Modal opens when \"Check Stock\" is clicked\necho ✅ Table with columns: Product Name, Category, Stock, Rating\necho ✅ Color-coded stock badges (Green/Yellow/Red)\necho ✅ Star ratings with review counts\necho ✅ \"Refresh Data\" button to update information\necho ✅ Responsive design for mobile devices\necho.\necho ============================================================================\necho 🐛 COMMON ISSUES AND SOLUTIONS:\necho ============================================================================\necho.\necho ISSUE: Button not visible\necho SOLUTION: Clear cache, restart servers, check console errors\necho.\necho ISSUE: \"No ratings\" showing for all products\necho SOLUTION: Check if reviews exist in database, verify API endpoint\necho.\necho ISSUE: Stock not updating after purchases\necho SOLUTION: Stock updates automatically when orders are placed\necho.\necho ISSUE: Modal not opening\necho SOLUTION: Check JavaScript console for errors\necho.\necho ============================================================================\necho 🔍 DEBUG STEPS:\necho ============================================================================\necho.\necho 1. Open browser DevTools (F12)\necho 2. Go to Console tab\necho 3. Click \"Check Stock\" button\necho 4. Look for these debug messages:\necho    - \"Fetched products: [array of products]\"\necho    - \"Ratings response for product X: 200\"\necho    - \"Ratings data for product X: [array of ratings]\"\necho    - \"Final stock data with ratings: [processed data]\"\necho.\necho If you see errors, copy them and check the API endpoints.\necho.\necho ============================================================================\necho Press any key to continue...\npause > nul